abstract = {This chapter explores the role of virtual intelligent characters, AGI (artificial general intelligence), and ASI (artificial superintelligence) in the future of the Metaverse along the parallel tracks of speculative fiction and current technology innovation. This includes looking back at speculative fiction narratives of artificial intelligence (AI), comparing embodied AI to virtual AI, and the history of chatbots and NPCs, which are intertwined regarding the future of virtually intelligent characters, now becoming known as SmartNPCs or generative agents. The current landscape of intelligent characters is explored, as well as several architectures that distinguish a full virtual character with an identity, virtual body, and a virtual landscape to explore from simple LLMs like ChatGPT. Several recent developments, including societies of SmartNPCs or generative agents, are explored. Looking toward the future, the chapter examines how virtual intelligent characters may lead the vanguard toward AGI because of their ability, unlike disembodied AI, to have experiences and build memories, both with human-based avatars and other AI characters in the virtual environments. The role of these characters in navigating the digital landscape in general and the Metaverse in particular, as well as the fears that AGI may lead to superintelligence, including the speculative fiction tropes that led to such worries, wrap up the chapter.}
